# https://lwn.net/Articles/625072/
# > Yes you can page through it with space - which causes the current page
# > to vanish and be replaced by the next page.

# I find the single biggest usability improvement to GNU Info is to turn this
# behaviour off.  If the documentation is going to be split up into separate
# chapters (which I don't find particularly annoying, to be honest), then
# it's better to not have the viewer jump between chapters and completely
# refresh the screen when you're not expecting it to.

#var
scroll-behaviour=Page Only

# Then run infokey to compile that to ~/.info.
